<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/178:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-07">October 7, 1919</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                                7—5:57 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>128. For Polk from Bandholtz. Seals on museum doors are as yet
                            undisturbed. Roumanians have delivered 1,000 serviceable rifles for the
                            police. Evacuation of western Hungary should end today. Colonel Moore
                            has reported and order will be issued at once returning Colonel Horowitz
                            to Paris.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bandholtz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>